{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id79e26e8e-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s3871f"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3871f"},"text":"§ 3871f.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Critical conservation areas","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id79e26e8f-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s3871f/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Definitions","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"In this section:","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id79e26e90-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s3871f/a/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Critical conservation area","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The term “critical conservation area” means a geographical area that contains a critical conservation condition that can be addressed through the program.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id79e26e91-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s3871f/a/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Priority resource concern","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"The term “priority resource concern” means a natural resource concern located in a critical conservation area that can be addressed through—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id79e26e92-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s3871f/a/2/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" water quality improvement, including through reducing erosion, promoting sediment control, and addressing nutrient management activities affecting large bodies of water of regional, national, or international significance;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id79e26e93-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s3871f/a/2/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" water quantity improvement, including improvement relating to—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"id79e26e94-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s3871f/a/2/B/i"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"i"},"text":"(i)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" drought;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"id79e26e95-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s3871f/a/2/B/ii"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"ii"},"text":"(ii)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" groundwater, surface water, aquifer, or other water sources; or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"id79e26e96-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s3871f/a/2/B/iii"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"iii"},"text":"(iii)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" water retention and flood prevention;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id79e26e97-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s3871f/a/2/C"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"C"},"text":"(C)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" wildlife habitat restoration to address species of concern at a Federal, State, or local level; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id79e26e98-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s3871f/a/2/D"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"D"},"text":"(D)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" other natural resource improvements, as determined by the Secretary, within the critical conservation area.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id79e26e99-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s3871f/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Applications","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In administering funds under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t16/s3871d/d/2"},"text":"section 3871d(d)(2) of this title","children":[],"tail":", the Secretary shall select applications for partnership agreements and program contracts within critical conservation areas designated under this section that address 1 or more priority resource concerns for which the critical conservation area is designated."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id79e26e9a-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s3871f/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Critical conservation area designations","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id79e26e9b-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s3871f/c/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" In general","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Secretary shall identify 1 or more priority resource concerns that apply to each critical conservation area designated under this section after ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2014-02-07"},"text":"February 7, 2014","children":[],"tail":", including the conservation goals and outcomes sufficient to demonstrate that progress is being made to address the priority resource concern."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id79e26e9c-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s3871f/c/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Priority","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"In designating critical conservation areas under this section, the Secretary shall give priority to geographical areas based on the degree to which the geographical area—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id79e26e9d-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s3871f/c/2/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" includes multiple States with significant agricultural production;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id79e26e9e-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s3871f/c/2/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" is covered by an existing regional, State, binational, or multistate agreement or plan that has established objectives, goals, and work plans and is adopted by a Federal, State, or regional authority;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id79e26e9f-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s3871f/c/2/C"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"C"},"text":"(C)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" contains 1 or more priority resource concerns; or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id79e26ea0-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s3871f/c/2/D"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"D"},"text":"(D)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" contains producers that need assistance in meeting or avoiding the need for a natural resource regulatory requirement that could have a negative impact on the economic scope of the agricultural operations within the area.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id79e26ea1-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s3871f/c/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Review and withdrawal","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"The Secretary may—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id79e26ea2-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s3871f/c/3/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" review designations of critical conservation areas under this section not more frequently than once every 5 years; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id79e26ea3-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s3871f/c/3/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" withdraw designation of a critical conservation area only if the Secretary determines that the area is no longer a critical conservation area.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id79e26ea4-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s3871f/c/4"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"(4)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Limitation","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Secretary may not designate more than 8 geographical areas as critical conservation areas under this section.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id79e26ea5-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s3871f/d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"d"},"text":"(d)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Outreach to eligible partners and producers","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Secretary shall provide outreach and education to eligible partners and producers in critical conservation areas designated under this section to encourage the development of projects to address each priority resource concern identified by the Secretary for that critical conservation area.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id79e26ea6-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s3871f/e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"e"},"text":"(e)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Administration","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id79e26ea7-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s3871f/e/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" In general","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Except as provided in paragraph (2), the Secretary shall administer any partnership agreement or program contract under this section in a manner that is consistent with the terms of the program.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id79e26ea8-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s3871f/e/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Relationship to existing activity","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Secretary shall, to the maximum extent practicable, ensure that eligible activities carried out in critical conservation areas designated under this section complement and are consistent with other Federal and State programs and water quality and quantity strategies.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id79e26ea9-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/198/tXII/s1271F"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–198, title XII, § 1271F","children":[],"tail":", as added "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/113/79/tII/s2401"},"text":"Pub. L. 113–79, title II, § 2401","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2014-02-07"},"text":"Feb. 7, 2014","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/128/750"},"text":"128 Stat. 750","children":[],"tail":"; amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/334/tII/s2707"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–334, title II, § 2707","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2018-12-20"},"text":"Dec. 20, 2018","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/132/4600"},"text":"132 Stat. 4600","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id79e26eaa-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id79e26eab-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id79e26eac-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2018—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/334/s2707/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–334, § 2707(2)","children":[],"tail":", added subsec. (a). Former subsec. (a) redesignated (b)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/334/s2707/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–334, § 2707(1)","children":[],"tail":", (3), redesignated subsec. (a) as (b), in heading, substituted “Applications” for “In general”, and, in text, substituted “3871d(d)(2)” for “3871d(d)(3)” and “program contracts” for “producer contracts” and inserted “that address 1 or more priority resource concerns for which the critical conservation area is designated” before period at end. Former subsec. (b) redesignated (c)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/334/s2707/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–334, § 2707(1)","children":[],"tail":", redesignated subsec. (b) as (c). Former subsec. (c) redesignated (e)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c)(1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/334/s2707/4/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–334, § 2707(4)(B)","children":[],"tail":", added par. (1). Former par. (1) redesignated (2)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c)(2). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/334/s2707/4/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–334, § 2707(4)(A)","children":[],"tail":", (C), redesignated par. (1) as (2), added subpar. (C), redesignated subpar. (E) as (D), and struck out former subpars. (C) and (D) which read as follows:"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(C) would benefit from water quality improvement, including through reducing erosion, promoting sediment control, and addressing nutrient management activities affecting large bodies of water of regional, national, or international significance;","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(D) would benefit from water quantity improvement, including improvement relating to—","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(i) groundwater, surface water, aquifer, or other water sources; or","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(ii) a need to promote water retention and flood prevention; or”.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c)(3). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/334/s2707/4/D"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–334, § 2707(4)(D)","children":[],"tail":", added par. (3) and struck out former par. (3). Prior to amendment, text read as follows: “Critical conservation area designations under this section shall expire after 5 years, subject to redesignation, except that the Secretary may withdraw designation from an area if the Secretary finds the area no longer meets the conditions described in paragraph (1).”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/334/s2707/4/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–334, § 2707(4)(A)","children":[],"tail":", redesignated par. (2) as (3). Former par. (3) redesignated (4)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c)(4). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/334/s2707/4/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–334, § 2707(4)(A)","children":[],"tail":", redesignated par. (3) as (4)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (d). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/334/s2707/5"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–334, § 2707(5)","children":[],"tail":", added subsec. (d)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (e). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/334/s2707/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–334, § 2707(1)","children":[],"tail":", redesignated subsec. (c) as (e)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (e)(1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/334/s2707/6/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–334, § 2707(6)(A)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “program contract” for “producer contract”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (e)(3). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/334/s2707/6/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–334, § 2707(6)(B)","children":[],"tail":", struck out par. (3). Text read as follows: “For a critical conservation area described in subsection (b)(1)(D), the Secretary may use authorities under the Watershed Protection and Flood Prevention Act ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t16/s1001"},"text":"16 U.S.C. 1001","children":[],"tail":" et seq.), other than section 14 of such Act ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t16/s1012"},"text":"16 U.S.C. 1012","children":[],"tail":"), to carry out projects for the purposes of this section.”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
